         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>To emperor Caesar Marcus Aurelius Severus <supplied reason="lost">Alexander</supplied> <note>erased</note> Pius Felis Augustus <supplied reason="lost">and Julia Mamaea Augusta, mother of Augustus</supplied> <note>erased</note> and of the camps. Marcus A<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/> <supplied reason="lost">centurion of Legion III Augusta pia vindex <note>erased</note> Sev</supplied>eriana, placed in command of the detachment of the same legion, built the fort from its foundations, using the same detachment.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>ll. 1, 3-4. Erased after Alexander's <foreign xml:lang="la">damnatio</foreign> in 235.</p>
            <p>l.6. It is not certain whether the erasure of the name of the legion is deliberate and is to be attributed to its damnatio in 238.</p>
         </div>
